\begin_layout Subsection*

\lang english
1.
 Purpose
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
The purpose of this policy is to establish the operational framework for real-time monitoring and event management within the Elko County Information Operations Department.
 This policy governs how the Department monitors IT services,
 infrastructure,
 endpoints,
 and applications;
 classifies events according to a defined taxonomy;
 and routes events to the appropriate response path.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
This policy shall govern real-time detection and operational response:
 collecting monitoring data,
 classifying events,
 generating work orders for actionable conditions,
 and ensuring that threshold breaches feed the capacity and availability investigation process defined in 
\series bold
Policy 
