\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsection*

\lang english
2.
 Scope
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
This policy applies to all Information Operations Department personnel and governs the real-time monitoring of all IT services,
 infrastructure,
 endpoints,
 and applications administered by the Department.
 In-scope data collection types include availability and ping checks,
 performance metrics (CPU utilization,
 memory utilization,
 disk utilization,
 and application response times),
 flow data (NetFlow and sFlow),
 syslog and event logs from network equipment and servers,
 and SNMP polling.
 All events generated by the monitoring function shall be classified under the event taxonomy defined in Section 6.2 of this policy.
\end_layout

